# Commit conventions

All commits **must** use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/)
form:

```text
<type>(<optional scope>): <short summary>
```

## Title (first line)

- **Format:** `type(scope): subject` — scope is optional but preferred
  when the change is localized (e.g. `contract-artefacts`, `cli-kit`, `docs`).
- **Length:** no more than **100** characters.
- **Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`,
  `build` — use the closest match.
- **Subject:** imperative mood, lowercase after the colon (no trailing
  period).

Examples:

```text
feat(contract-artefacts): add forge-config mixin and path discovery
docs: document contracts checkout root in ADR-0002
ci: enforce citty and Bun.spawn policies in workflow
```

## Body

- Separate from the title with a **blank line**.
- Wrap lines at **72** characters or fewer.
- Explain **why**, not a file list.
- Never include `Co-Authored-By` lines.

## Author

Use only the repository's configured git user as the commit author.
